American Express in card deal with Bradesco . American Express and Bradesco , Brazil ' s largest private bank , said on Thursday that Bradesco agreed to sell American Express cards through its branch network . Over the past two years , American Express said it has concluded agreements with several financial institutions worldwide to issue and sell American Express Cards . Overseas banks issuing American Express cards include Israel ' s Bank Hapoalim , Banco Comercial Portugues ( Portugal ) , Alpha Credit Bank in Greece , Turkey ' s Akbank , Tong Yang Card Corp ( South Korea ) , and Banco Consolidado ( Venezuela ) . 
